8 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Department rulemaking -- fees. (1) The department may adopt rules
9 necessary to implement [sections 1 through 4].
10 (2) The fees collected under [sections 1 through 4] in accordance with 37-1-134 must be deposited
11 in a special revenue account for administration and enforcement of [sections 1 through 4].
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 3. License to practice home inspections required -- qualifications. (1)
14 An individual may not practice home inspection without a home inspector license issued under Title 37, chapter
15 1, and [sections 1 through 4].
16 (2) An applicant for a home inspection license must have:
17 (a) successfully completed a minimum of 40 hours of comprehensive home inspection instruction
18 approved by the department;
19 (b) membership in a national home inspection association; and
20 (c) a minimum of $100,000 liability insurance coverage in errors and omissions insurance.
21 (3) The requirements in subsections (2)(b) and (2)(c) of this section must be maintained for
22 continued licensure.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Standards of home inspection practice. (1) A home inspector shall
25 issue a written home inspection report to a client after completing a home inspection unless the client agrees in
26 writing to release the home inspector from this obligation.
27 (2) The home inspection report must clearly identify and describe:
28 (a) the inspected systems, structures, and other relevant components of the dwelling;
- 2 - Authorized Print Version – HB 225

